rs per galaxy with these current facilities. We\ninvestigate a 'minimal' ngVLA configuration, removing the longest baselines and\nmuch of the very compact core, and find good imaging can still be performed at\n1 kpc resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Oct 2018 14:43:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-12"}
